<span id="v.iii.xii-p2"></span><span class="c12"><span
id="v.iii.xii-p2.1"></span>Hermas <span
id="fr_2385"></span>[2386](#fn_2385.md) </span>  <span
id="fr_2386"></span>[2387](#fn_2386.md) whom the apostle Paul mentions in
writing to the Romans “Salute <span id="fr_2387"></span>[2388](#fn_2387.md)
Phlegon, Hermes, Patrobas, Hermas <span
id="fr_2388"></span>[2389](#fn_2388.md) and the brethren that are with
them” <span id="fr_2389"></span>[2390](#fn_2389.md) is reputed to be the
author of the book which is called *Pastor* and which is also read
publicly in some churches of Greece. It is in fact a useful book and
many of the ancient writers quote from it as authority, but among the
Latins it is almost unknown.

