<span id="v.iii.xii-p3"></span> The date of Hermas depends on what
Hermas is supposed to be the author. He is supposed to be 1 the Hermas
of the New Testament, or 2 the brother of Pius I (139–54) or 3 a still
later Hermas. All these views have distinguished advocates, but this
view of Jerome taken from Origen through Eusebius is not much accepted.

